      "is_mcp": false,
      "arguments": {
        "file_path": "/workspace/answer.json",
        "old_string": "  \"text\": \"The Rust compiler and Servo browser engine share code through the Stylo shared styling library. In servo/servo, the root Cargo.toml (lines 160, 178) declares external git dependencies on https://github.com/servo/stylo for the 'selectors' and 'style' crates. The components/layout/Cargo.toml and components/script/Cargo.toml both depend on these workspace crates. The layout/lib.rs file imports from the style module (lines 42-43) for WritingMode and ComputedValues, serving as the main entry point for the style system. The script/lib.rs file macro-uses stylo_atoms (line 21). In rust-lang/rust, the standard library proc_macro crate at library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs exports the proc_macro bridge public module (line 41), with the actual bridge interface defined in library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs. This bridge provides the RPC API for communicating between proc macro crates (like those used by Servo's build system) and the Rust compiler frontend. Servo does not directly depend on rust-lang/rust crates; rather, any Servo build scripts that use procedural macros would use the standard rust proc_macro bridge from the Rust standard library.\"",
        "new_string": "The Rust compiler and Servo browser engine share code through the Stylo shared styling library. In servo/servo, the root Cargo.toml (lines 160, 178) declares external git dependencies on https://github.com/servo/stylo for the 'selectors' and 'style' crates. These crates are re-exported via workspace dependencies in components/layout/Cargo.toml (line 49) and components/script/Cargo.toml (line 129). The layout/lib.rs file (lines 42-43) imports directly from the style module for WritingMode and ComputedValues, serving as the main entry point for the style system. The script/lib.rs file (line 21) macro-uses stylo_atoms. In rust-lang/rust, the standard library proc_macro crate is defined at library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs and exports a public bridge module (line 41). The bridge interface is defined at library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs and provides the RPC API for communication between proc macro crates and the Rust compiler frontend. The compiler/rustc_expand/src/proc_macro.rs file (lines 17, 33-34) shows how the Rust compiler itself uses pm::bridge::server traits for executing procedural macros. The compiler/rustc_proc_macro/Cargo.toml (line 13) re-exports the stdlib proc_macro implementation at library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs. The selectors crate from Stylo is used throughout Servo: layout/replaced.rs uses selectors::Element, layout/dom_traversal.rs uses selectors::Element, and script/dom/node.rs uses selectors for bloom filters and selector matching. Servo does not directly depend on rust-lang/rust crates; rather, any Servo build scripts using procedural macros would use the standard Rust proc_macro bridge.",
        "replace_all": false
